item.title: Which one is better to use C# or vb.NET
item.dc:creator: @CodyPkz1 CodyPkz™
item.description:
@CodyPkz1 wrote:

They both have the same dependencies but C# has a different syntax that’s also used in C++
Here’s my application using the element function:

[code] private void button1_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
webBrowser1.Document.GetElementById(“ip”).SetAttribute(“value”, textBox1.Text);

        webBrowser1.Document.GetElementById("time").SetAttribute("value", textBox2.Text);

        webBrowser1.Document.Forms[0].InvokeMember("submit");

MessageBox.Show(“It Worked!”);

    }
}

}[/code]

In VB it wouldnt require the semi colin or the syntax {
Also it’s more closer to java then it is .NET
